# Patch 09 -- GitHub Actions CI workflow

**Target path:** `~/crm/.github/workflows/ci.yml` (new file)
**Action:** New file. No existing CI to merge with.

---

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]
  push:
    branches: [main]

# Avoid concurrent runs on the same branch / PR.
concurrency:
  group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}
  cancel-in-progress: true

jobs:
  verify:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    timeout-minutes: 15

    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Setup pnpm
        uses: pnpm/action-setup@v4
        with:
          version: 8

      - name: Setup Node
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version-file: '.nvmrc'
          cache: 'pnpm'

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: pnpm install --frozen-lockfile

      - name: Typecheck
        run: pnpm typecheck

      - name: Lint
        run: pnpm lint

      - name: Test (with coverage)
        run: pnpm test --coverage
        env:
          # Dummy env values that match vitest.config.ts defineConfig.test.env
          # (so tests don't need real Supabase / Resend creds in CI).
          NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL: http://localhost:54321
          NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: dummy_anon_key
          SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY: dummy_service_role_key
          RESEND_API_KEY: dummy_resend_key
          OWNER_USER_ID: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

      # Optional: post coverage as a PR comment.
      # - name: Coverage report
      #   uses: davelosert/vitest-coverage-report-action@v2
```

---

## Notes

- `--frozen-lockfile` ensures the lockfile is in sync with `package.json`; CI fails if a PR updates `package.json` but not `pnpm-lock.yaml`.
- The dummy env values mirror what `vitest.config.ts` already sets in `test.env`. Confirm the list against the live config before landing.
- This workflow does NOT deploy. Vercel's GitHub integration handles deploys separately.

---

## Pre-land checklist

- [ ] `.nvmrc` lands first (Patch 08), so `node-version-file: '.nvmrc'` resolves.
- [ ] Repo has `actions: write` permission for the default token (default in fresh repos; check `Settings -> Actions -> General`).
- [ ] First PR after landing must pass green; subsequent PRs are gated on it.

---

## Optional: branch protection

After the workflow has run green at least once on `main`, enable branch protection for `main`:

- Require PRs (no direct pushes).
- Require `verify` job to pass.
- Require linear history.

Land via `gh repo edit` or the GitHub web UI; not part of this patch.
